## Why This Is Asked

Tests understanding of a practical, low-level data structure and its wrap-around behavior, plus efficient empty/full checks in a simple producer/consumer path.

## Key Concepts

- Ring buffers
- Power-of-two masking
- Empty/full checks with head/tail without extra state
- SPSC memory ordering

## Code Example

```c
typedef struct {
  size_t head, tail;
  unsigned char data[N];
} Ring;

int enqueue(Ring *r, unsigned char value) {
  if ((r->head - r->tail) == N) return 0; // full
  r->data[r->head & (N - 1)] = value;
  r->head++;
  return 1;
}
int dequeue(Ring *r, unsigned char *out) {
  if (r->head == r->tail) return 0; // empty
  *out = r->data[r->tail & (N - 1)];
  r->tail++;
  return 1;
}
```

## Follow-up Questions

- How would you modify for multi-producer/multi-consumer?
- What memory-ordering considerations arise on weakly-ordered architectures?
